From 05e7222161d6083184bc71bec456c9dd9a476027 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vignesh Viswanathan <quic_viswanat@quicinc.com>
Date: Fri, 28 Feb 2025 17:24:17 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] serial: qcom-geni: Remove WARN_ON in serial_start_tx_fifo

In case where previous command was cancelled and left data in the tx
fifo, WARN_ON calls printk which tries to get uart_port_lock. However,
uart_core already holds the lock before calling start_tx_fifo leading to
a deadlock.

Fix this by removing the WARN_ON and handling this case by discarding
the data on the tx fifo.

Change-Id: I2d3cede6bb4516607fbd7e9b7a4352112745feed
Signed-off-by: Vignesh Viswanathan <quic_viswanat@quicinc.com>
---
 drivers/tty/serial/qcom_geni_serial.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/tty/serial/qcom_geni_serial.c b/drivers/tty/serial/qcom_geni_serial.c
index 88653208cc61..43b2ed74364f 100644
--- a/drivers/tty/serial/qcom_geni_serial.c
+++ b/drivers/tty/serial/qcom_geni_serial.c
@@ -666,7 +666,8 @@ static void qcom_geni_serial_start_tx_fifo(struct uart_port *uport)
 	if (!qcom_geni_serial_main_active(uport) &&
 	    !qcom_geni_serial_tx_empty(uport)) {
 		if (uart_circ_chars_pending(xmit)) {
-			WARN_ON(1);
+			c = xmit->buf[xmit->tail];
+			uart_xmit_advance(uport, 1);
 			writel(M_CMD_DONE_EN, uport->membase + SE_GENI_M_IRQ_CLEAR);
 			qcom_geni_serial_setup_tx(uport, 1);
 			writel(c, uport->membase + SE_GENI_TX_FIFOn);
-- 
